# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package: 2. Materials Science
# By Simon Gravelle, Mark A. Tschopp, Jacob R. Gissinger, and Axel Kohlmeyer
# Tutorial 4: 1. Surface energy and relaxation of the low-index aluminum surfaces
#
# Build an fcc aluminum slab with free surfaces normal to z, relax it, and
# evaluate the surface energy from the energy balance
#     gamma = (E_slab - N*Ecoh) / (2*A)
# The exposed face is selected with the index variable "face":
#     lmp -in alsurf.lmp -var face 110
# or via the Set Variables dialog of LAMMPS-GUI.  The reported interlayer
# relaxation d12 compares the spacing of the two outermost layers with the
# bulk layer spacing of the chosen face.
#
# NOTE the in-plane box spans: for the (111) face the number of cells along
# y MUST be a multiple of three, or the periodic images do not join up and
# the "surface" energy comes out several times too large (see the note in
# the tutorial text -- the same commensurability rule as for the stacking
# fault and grain boundary constructions).

# 1) Initialization
units metal
dimension 3
boundary p p s
atom_style atomic

# 2) System definition
variable face index 100          # exposed surface: 100 | 110 | 111
variable a0   index 4.08165      # Zhou EAM equilibrium value from Tutorial 1
variable ecoh index -3.5799987   # Zhou EAM cohesive energy from Tutorial 1
if "${face} == 100" then   "lattice fcc ${a0} orient x 1 0 0 orient y 0 1 0 orient z 0 0 1 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25"   "variable dlay equal ${a0}/2"   "variable ny equal 4" elif "${face} == 110"   "lattice fcc ${a0} orient x 0 0 1 orient y 1 -1 0 orient z 1 1 0 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25"   "variable dlay equal ${a0}/(2*sqrt(2.0))"   "variable ny equal 4" elif "${face} == 111"   "lattice fcc ${a0} orient x 1 -1 0 orient y 1 1 -2 orient z 1 1 1 origin 0.25 0.25 0.05"   "variable dlay equal ${a0}/sqrt(3.0)"   "variable ny equal 3" else   "print 'ERROR: face must be 100, 110, or 111'"   "quit 1"
lattice fcc ${a0} orient x 0 0 1 orient y 1 -1 0 orient z 1 1 0 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
lattice fcc 4.08165 orient x 0 0 1 orient y 1 -1 0 orient z 1 1 0 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.08165 5.7723248 5.7723248
variable dlay equal ${a0}/(2*sqrt(2.0))
variable dlay equal 4.08165/(2*sqrt(2.0))
variable ny equal 4
region box block 0 4 0 ${ny} 0 5
region box block 0 4 0 4 0 5
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.3266 23.089299 28.861624)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 672 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 -0.0028861624) to (16.3266 23.089299 28.86451)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds

# 3) Settings
pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * Al_zhou.eam.alloy Al
Reading eam/alloy potential file Al_zhou.eam.alloy with DATE: 2007-10-12

# 4) Monitoring
thermo 50
thermo_style custom step pe press fnorm

# 5) Surface energy of the bulk-terminated (unrelaxed) slab
run 0 post no
WARNING: No fixes with time integration, atoms won't move
For more information see https://docs.lammps.org/err0028 (src/verlet.cpp:60)
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
